On 4/19/03 9:43 PM, "Jasan Carsley" <type2-78(-at-)attbi.com> wrote:

> I just recently replaced my fuel gauge sender. Since then when I fill the tank
> the needle on the gauge only goes to about three quarters full. With the old
> sender the needle would go to full but then drop to empty at half full and no
> longer register. Could this new sender be faulty or is there a way to
> calibrate the fuel gauge? I know on the earlier bays there was a screw on the
> back of the gauge to calibrate it. Can anyone confirm that this screw is on my
> 78 before I have to take apart the instrument panel?

I think this screw you are talking about is on the fuel gauge vibrator and
should be the last thing you test.  Follow Jamie's procedure for testing the
system:

http://www.type2.com/library/misc/vwggauge.htm

If the vibrator is at fault, I have a used one for you. New ones are $35.

